Setting up Developer Enviornment on Windows:

1. Enable Developer Mode on Windows 10

2. Enable Linux Subsystem to allow for bash shell enviornment

3. Install your favorite Linux OS from Microsoft Store

IDE's & Programming Enviornment

1. Install Vistual Studio Community Edition and supporting tools such as Node.JS and C++ Build and Python as these are commonly used.

2. Java - Install the JDK from OpenJDK website by downloading the binaries and then setting the enviornment variable for JAVA_HOME
